[{"id":"VR003427","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a ray of light in two materials. The diagram consists of a rectangle, which represents a Glass block labeled “n equals 1.50,” and a dashed line through the center of the rectangle, perpendicular to the top side of the rectangle. The incident ray starts near the bottom of the rectangle, slightly to the right of the middle, and points upward and to the left, toward the dashed line. The angle of this incident ray to the dashed line is labeled theta sub i. The other ray extends out from the point where the first ray, the dashed line, and the top side of the rectangle meet. This ray moves upward and to the left. The angle of this ray to the dashed line is labeled theta sub r.\" height=\"247\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR003427.g01.png\" width=\"400\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In an optics experiment, students are given a laser light source, eye protection, and a glass block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n equals 1.50\"><math alttext=\"n equals 1.50\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1.50</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> . The students want to find the critical angle (angle of incidence above which total internal reflection occurs) at the glass-air boundary. They adjust the angle of incidence <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub i\"><math alttext=\"theta sub i\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of the laser beam in the glass and record the angle of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub r\"><math alttext=\"theta sub r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> in air, as shown in the figure. The results are shown in the table. Which of the following refinements to the procedure would best allow the students to more accurately estimate the critical angle?</p>\n\n<div class=\"table_wrapper\">\n<table class=\"tgroup cols:2\">\n\t<tbody class=\"tbody\">\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub i\"><math alttext=\"theta sub i\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub r\"><math alttext=\"theta sub r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0 degrees\"><math alttext=\"0 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>0</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0 degrees\"><math alttext=\"0 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>0</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"15 degrees\"><math alttext=\"15 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>15</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"23 degrees\"><math alttext=\"23 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>23</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"30 degrees\"><math alttext=\"30 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>30</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"49 degrees\"><math alttext=\"49 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>49</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"45 degrees\"><math alttext=\"45 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>45</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\">None</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr class=\"row\">\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"60 degrees\"><math alttext=\"60 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>60</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span></td>\n\t\t\t<td class=\"entry colname:col2\">None</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR003427_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Reverse the direction of the laser beam and have it go from air into the glass. Repeat the measurements of incident and refracted angles.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Use smaller increments of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub i\"><math alttext=\"theta sub i\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> between <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"30 degrees\"><math alttext=\"30 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>30</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"45 degrees\"><math alttext=\"45 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>45</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Have two groups independently perform the original procedure using the same incident angles and then average the results.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Take measurements at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"75 degrees\"><math alttext=\"75 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>75</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"90 degrees\"><math alttext=\"90 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>90</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":1}]